According to the observed Ripley’s K-functions (Fig. 3), in Eriyawetiya and 3rd Kurana study areas, dengue incidences were clustered at some scales and be dispersed at others. Significant clustering is detected within a radius of approximately 155 m and 125 m in Eriyawetiya and 3rd Kurana study areas, respectively and dispersion is observed afterwards.Figure 3
